data.description: SELLER IS OFFERING TO PAY CLOSING COST WITH ACCEPTABLE OFFER - If you want to live in the country but not to far from town this may be the home you are looking for.  Sitting on a 2.68-acre parcel of land, this 3400 square foot home features 4-bedrooms, 2.5-bathrooms, a nice size pantry, a large laundry room, three nice guest bedrooms, a large master bedroom and bathroom, an updated kitchen and two nice size living areas not to mention a sitting area off the kitchen with a wood burning fireplace and a wet bar.  Off the utility room you will find a very nice storage room with plenty of shelving so you can stock up on supplies.  The kitchen has been updated with granite countertops, new painted cabinets and appliances. The sellers have put a fresh coat of paint on the majority of the inside of the home updating its look.  Beyond the interior, this property features a 4-car garage, providing ample space for vehicles and storage. The backyard offers plenty of room for the kids to play. The patio, overlooking the property allows you to enjoy the outdoors in a private setting.  There is plenty of space for entertaining family and friends or simply enjoy a quiet evening on the patio overlooking the grounds.  A new roof was installed in 2020.  This home is located in flood zone X so no flood insurance is needed.  Don't miss the opportunity to own a wonderful country home.  Schedule your showing today!  Reserved items:  Dog kennel, washer/dryer, mini fridge on patio, freezer and icebox in garage, metal shelving in garage, all outside furniture and toys including swing set, drapes in master bedroom and den (the den you walk in to from outside garage area)
